Reasoning: The paper discusses machine learning methods for deriving vector-space embeddings of words and their success in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also evaluates the performance of the parallelogram model of analogy, which is a machine learning model, and thus could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
